Encapsulation
===============
-Binding the data and its operation of an entity is known as encapsulation.
-jar file are encapsulation packages.
-package are encapsulation of classes.
-class are encapsulation of methad and data.
real world example.
-------------------
capsul,pencile box,bag

real time example
-------------------
java bean class
-class must be public
-member variable  must be private
-public contructor
-public getter and setter.

example to understand encapsulation
=====================================
public class Main
{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    Student s=new Student();
	    s.setId(2);
	    s.setName("nisha");
	    s.setAddress("btm");
	    System.out.println("id="+s.getId()+" "+"name="+s.getName()+" "+"address="+s.getAddress());

	  	}
}
 class Student{
   private  int id;
   private  String name;
  private  String address;
    public Student(int id,String name,String address){
        this.id=id;
        this.name=name;
        this.address=address;
    }
    public Student(){
        
    }
    public int getId(){
        return id;
    }
    public void  setId(int id){
        this.id=id;
    }
      public String getName(){
        return name;
    }
    public void setName(String name){
        this.name=name;
    }
      public String getAddress(){
        return address;
    }
    public void setAddress(String address){
        this.address=address;
    }
}
